# Excalidraw Monorepo — Cursor Rules

This file provides Cursor AI with the top-level conventions for the Excalidraw codebase.
Detailed rules are in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`.

## Quick Reference

### Stack
- TypeScript (strict-ish), React 19, Vite 5, Vitest 3, Yarn Workspaces
- State: Jotai (via `editor-jotai` / `app-jotai` — never import `jotai` directly)
- Styling: SCSS modules co-located with components
- Crypto: Web Crypto API / AES-GCM (see `packages/excalidraw/data/encryption.ts`)

### Package Boundaries (CRITICAL)
- `packages/*` = library code — zero Firebase / socket.io / env-var dependencies
- `excalidraw-app/` = app layer — Firebase, collab, sharing live here only

### TypeScript
- `import type` for all type-only imports (ESLint enforced)
- `catch (error: unknown)` — never `any` in catch clauses
- `readonly` arrays for element collections
- Math points: always `Point` from `@excalidraw/math`, never `{ x, y }` inline

### Security (non-negotiable)
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without DOMPurify
- Validate URL protocol before `window.open` / `location.href`
- Crypto = `window.crypto.subtle` only; never `Math.random()` for security
- Secrets in `import.meta.env.VITE_APP_*` only, never hardcoded

### Testing
- Co-locate tests: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts` in the same directory
- Coverage floor: lines 60%, branches 70%, functions 63%, statements 60%
- Run: `yarn test:app --watch=false` | `yarn test:typecheck` | `yarn test:code`

### Commits
Format: `type(scope): description`
Types: feat | fix | chore | refactor | test | docs | style | perf | ci

### Commands
```bash
yarn start                  # dev server
yarn test:all               # full CI suite (typecheck + lint + prettier + tests)
yarn test:typecheck         # tsc only
yarn test:code              # eslint
yarn test:other             # prettier
yarn test:app --watch=false # vitest
yarn build:packages         # build all packages in order
```

## Detailed Rules

See `.cursor/rules/`:
- `monorepo-conventions.mdc` — workspace layout, imports, file naming, commits
- `typescript-conventions.mdc` — type imports, any/unknown, immutability, naming
- `testing-standards.mdc` — test framework, coverage, helpers, co-location
- `security-rules.mdc` — XSS, URL validation, crypto, secrets, eval
- `excalidraw-app.mdc` — app-specific architecture, Firebase, collab, env vars
